(4) And somehow last night, I finally realized why prison reform and ending mass incarceration strikes so deeply with me - my favorite part of nursing is helping people feel human, and stay human, on the worst and most vulnerable days of their lives.

(3) Death by incarceration is very real. People are locked away and forgotten about, dehumanized, statistics in a system that profits from a modern day form of slavery - an extension of structural racism.
